  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a low heat</p><p>Crush your <strong>cardamom pods</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife</p><p>Once the butter has melted, add the <strong>cardamom</strong> <strong>seeds</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1110.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1110.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1110.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1110.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1110.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>shallot</strong> (save the rest for later!) and your <strong>garam masala</strong> to the pan</p><p>Increase the heat to medium and cook for 2-3 min or until softened</p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1110.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1110.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1110.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1110.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1110.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the shallot is cooking, chop your <strong>sultanas</strong> roughly</p><p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 175ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[230ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Rice-in-pot-with-water-1688043804015-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Rice-in-pot-with-water-1688043804015-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Rice-in-pot-with-water-1688043804015-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Rice-in-pot-with-water-1688043804015-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Rice-in-pot-with-water-1688043804015-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the shallot has softened, increase the heat to high, add your <strong>lamb mince </strong>and<strong> </strong>cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped sultanas</strong>,<strong> chopped garlic </strong>and<strong> tomato paste </strong>and cook for 1 min further</p><p>Add 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[340ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>with your <strong>beef stock mix </strong>and<strong> </strong>season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> then cook for 5-6 min or until thickened slightly</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
